
= Smooth skinning

div::[font-size:90%; line-height:1.5em;]

* **Linear Blend Skinning** (LBS): Linear interpolation of positions between associated frames

div::[height:25px;]::

* Example at middle vertex position of a bending cylinder
** \(p=0.5\,p_{|b1}+0.5\,p_{|b2}\)
** \(p=0.5\,\underbrace{\mathrm{M}_1\,(\mathrm{M}_1^0)^{-1}}_{\mathrm{T}_1}\, p^0+0.5\,\underbrace{\mathrm{M}_2\,(\mathrm{M}_2^0)^{-1}}_{\mathrm{T}_2}\,p^0\)
** \(p=(0.5\,\mathrm{T}_1+0.5\,\mathrm{T}_2)\,p^0\)




div::[height:50px;]::

* Can be generalized to arbitrary interpolation between two bones
** \(p = \alpha\, p_{|b1} + (1-\alpha)\,p_{|b2}= \left(\alpha \mathrm{T}_1 + (1-\alpha)\,\mathrm{T}_2\right)\,p^0\)
** \(\alpha\): skinning weights

div::[height:50px;]::

* Can be generalized to any number of bones


** <div class="border"> \(\displaystyle p = \sum_{j=0}^{N-1} \alpha_j\;p_{|bj} = \left(\sum_{j=0}^{N-1} \alpha_j \, \mathrm{T}_j\right)\,p^0 \) </div> \(\,\), \(\;\;\displaystyle \sum_j \alpha_j=1\)


